I'll argue forcefully for answer A (6):

The problem directly asks how many more books Peter has read compared to his brother. The calculation is straightforward: Peter reads 40% of 20 books (8 books), while his brother reads 10% of 20 books (2 books). The difference is precisely 6 books - 8 minus 2 equals 6.

